<Content>Giant Rooms The Boston Hilton Financial District is an elegant hotel in a great location with helpful staff. The lobby is beautiful with a well-appointed library and free coffee in the morning and cider in the evening. You need a room key to access upper floors from the elevator which adds a feeling of security. The rooms are enormous. The ceiling height is phenomenal. The views (and we were only on the 6th floor of 15) were fantastic. We had booked two rooms for our family of five, but easily could have fit into one room. One of our rooms was a corner room and I think it was as big as three other hotel rooms would have been. We were hoping for connecting rooms, but they don't have those at all. That was our only disappointment with the hotel. The building is very old and solidly built, so once you close your door, you hear nothing from hallways, rooms next door or rooms above.The rooms were well decorated and the beds were very comfortable. We had free breakfast passes and thoroughly enjoyed the buffet. The staff at the restaurant and throughout the hotel were very helpful. They even let us borrow a screwdriver which we needed to put together a Christmas present (not to fix anything in our room, don't worry).The hotel is right across from restaurants and bars and cafes and only a few blocks from Quincy Market, the Freedom Trail and the Aquarium. It was an easy walk to South Station and fairly close to the Children's Museum. We could easily have walked to the Common, the North End or the USS Constition.I would highly recommend staying at the Boston Hilton Financial District. 
