<Content>Wyndham - Great Location! My husband and I just returned from a 4-day weekend in Boston and had a great time. We stayed at the Boston Wyndham and found it was close to many of the attractions, especially Fanueil Hall/Quincy Market. We took many of the reviewers' advice and signed up for the Wyndham By Request. We were able to check-in at 10:30am when we arrived and later in the afternoon received our complimentary snack and drink. The staff was very friendly and always willing to help with any questions. The only thing we found that our room did not have were drawers to keep our clothes in, so we had to live out of our suitcases. Other than that, our room was very clean and quiet. Some suggestions for those going for a long weekend trip....Book the Beantown Trolley Tour. It is the only 2-day tour you can get on and off the trolley at the different stops. Buy your tickets at the Wharf, not the concierge - they only have 1-day passes. We used this as our main transportation for the first two days and we saw basically everything without getting too overwhelmed. Walking the Freedom Trail also helped.If you go to Salem, take the Trolley Tour. This gives you the basic idea of the city and you can get on and off the trolley. You will have to take the train to get to Salem, too. This was very easy and the concierge gave us train times and directions. If you are looking for a few nice dinner restaurants, we loved Legal Seafood (at the Wharf) and Plaza III Kansas City Steakhouse (at Fanueil Hall/South Market). Both were very good. Plaza III is pricey, but well worth the money! Also, if you are going during baseball season, you will have to buy a Red Sox hat, T-shirt, etc. It is all over the city and you will defintely catch the fever! Go to a game, too. It was so much fun and there are plenty of bars around the park to go to before and after (Game On and Cask 'n Flagon were our favorites). 
