<Content>Nice Hotel but noisy We just came back from a visit to Boston and a stay at the Wyndham Boston. The hotel is nice--we had a nice room with a King size bed on an upper floor. Like many hotels, the bathroom could be layed out better with a little more room. We must agree with some of the previous posts regarding the outside noise. They leave a note in each room apologizing for the jackhammers that wake you up very early 6 days a week and can be heard loud and clear from the upper floors. Also, be aware--there are clubs on seemingly all sides of the hotel. If you are a sound sleeper, most likely you will sleep through the noise. The club on our side of the hotel got very noisy between 1 a.m and 2 a.m every night. We ate breakfast in the hotel every morning--it wasn't cheap--$13.50 per person for the very limited buffet and on Saturday when more people dine there, the staff is overworked and overwhelmed. There are no soda machines anywhere in the hotel--this is by design, I'm sure--so that you have to get one from the overpriced mini-bar. As others mentioned, Quincy Market is a short walk away, so buy your sodas or coffees there. Otherwise, the room was kept clean--maid service was generally excellent but one day the maid didn't leave any bottled water or a bath mat. Plus when people order room service, the trays tend to stay out in the hallway for several hours! We're Wyndham by Requests members--the welcome food packet is stingy here--just crackers and rondelet. We were at another Wyndham where we were given much more--but still it was nice to have free long distance calls. Overall, we would stay there again--it's hard to find a place in downtown Boston that isn't noisy. Too bad--there was once was a time when they rolled up the streets there at 6 p.m.! But perhaps, with the jackhammers nearby, for now, the Wyndham Boston is somewhat noisier . . . 
